org.tms.api

Interface Taggable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Cell, Column, Derivable, Row, Subset, Table, TableElement, TableRowColumnElement

    public interface Taggable
    Methods that allow TableElements to be selectively tagged. Tags are short strings that can be assigned and removed from TableElements to classify, identify, and otherwise differentiate tables, rows, columns, subsets, and cells.

    Since:
    "1.1"
    Version:
    "1.1"

        tags - the tag(s) to remove from this element
        Returns:

      • isTagged

        boolean isTagged(String... tags)
        Returns true if this taggable table element is tagged with the specified tag(s). If tags is null, returns true if the element contains any tags.
        Parameters:
        tags - the specified tag(s) to check for, or null
        Returns:
        true if the TableElement is tagged with the specified tag(s)

      • setTags

        void setTags(String... tags)
        Replaces the tag(s) on this Taggable element with those supplied. If tags is null, all tags are removed.
        Parameters:
        tags - the new set of tags to apply to this Taggable element

      • getTags

        String[] getTags()
        Returns the tag(s) assigned to this Taggable element.
        Returns:
        String array of tags that have been applied to this Taggable element
